@flexiarg eoi-engine/tension-free-solo-rule
@title EoI Tension Prompt — August-2026 Free-Solo Rule Honesty
@keywords eoi, free-solo, application-policy, address-now, applications-as-relief-fallacy, strawman-diagnostic
@audience operators authoring outward EoIs while holding a publicly-stated no-grants-no-VC-no-job-apps stance
@tone diagnostic-prompt
@references [eoi-engine/eoi-outward-one-shot, eoi-engine/tension-foreclosure, structure/whose-question-is-this]


! conclusion:
  When an outward EoI is being authored while the author holds a
  publicly-stated rule against applying (e.g. Joe's August-2026
  free-solo policy: no grants, no VC, no job applications), the EoI
  must address the rule honestly: either (a) state that the
  application is the considered output of a phase-space MAP, not
  application-as-relief-from-uncertainty, or (b) state that the
  rule is being re-examined in light of a specific surfaced
  alternative, or (c) name that the rule applies and this is the
  exception and why. What the EoI must not do: pretend the rule
  does not exist.

  + context:
    Applies during `address-now` tagging of an EoI Tension on outward
    applications written under a no-apply stance. The prompt asks: do
    you flag the rule to the recipient, or do you not? If yes, in what
    framing? If no, what makes this exception coherent under the rule's
    spirit?

  + IF:
    The author's public stance (or stance known to plausible recipients)
    includes a no-application rule, AND the artefact being authored is
    an application.

  + HOWEVER:
    The rule's framing inside the EoI itself is calibrated by who the
    recipient is and what they already know. If the rule is not
    publicly visible to this recipient, raising it pre-emptively may
    look performative; if it is publicly visible, omitting it looks
    evasive.

  + THEN:
    Author chooses one of routes (a) / (b) / (c) and writes a short
    rule-honesty paragraph in their own register.

  + BECAUSE:
    Per structure/whose-question-is-this: the EoI is the author's
    speech-act, in inhabited mode. Pretending the rule does not exist
    is consultant-voice; naming it honestly is operator-voice. The
    Right Speech discipline requires the latter.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    Author drafts the rule-honesty paragraph; eoi-engine assembly
    inserts or omits it per the author's chosen route; reviewer checks
    that the framing matches the recipient's actual visibility.

! source-note:
  Minted 2026-05-11 as part of the Arxana Essays annotation flow for
  the Anthropic Institute first-draft, alongside tension-foreclosure
  and tension-cv-shape. Surfaced from the strawman's diagnostic 3
  for that case (Mama-Claude's a/b/c options for the August-2026
  free-solo rule).
